{"title":"How do I reverse a list in Python?","body":"I have a list `[1,2,3]` and want `[3,2,1]`.","site":"stackoverflow","answers":[{"is_accepted":true,"score":142,"author":"alice","body":"Use `list.reverse()` or `reversed(list)`.","comments":[{"author":"bob","body":"Also `list[::-1]` for a copy"},{"author":"carol","body":"reverse() is in-place"}]},{"is_accepted":false,"score":87,"author":"dave","body":"You can also use `sorted()` with `reverse=True`.","comments":[]},{"is_accepted":false,"score":23,"author":"eve","body":"Numpy has `np.flip()`.","comments":[]},{"is_accepted":false,"score":5,"author":"frank","body":"Manual loop works too.","comments":[]}]}